title: Google\Cloud\Dataplex\V1\Entity
name: Entity
description:
Represents tables and fileset metadata contained within a zone.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataplex.v1.Entity

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.description: Constructor.

params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. The resource name of the entity, of the form: projects/{project_number}/locations/{location_id}/lakes/{lake_id}/zones/{zone_id}/entities/{id}.

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: Optional. Display name must be shorter than or equal to 63 characters.

params.name: data.description
params.description: Optional. User friendly longer description text. Must be shorter than or equal to 1024 characters.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Output only. The time when the entity was created.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. The time when the entity was last updated.

params.name: data.id
params.description: Required. A user-provided entity ID. It is mutable, and will be used as the published table name. Specifying a new ID in an update entity request will override the existing value. The ID must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), and underscores. Must begin with a letter.

params.name: data.etag
params.description: Optional. The etag for this entity. Required for update and delete requests. Must match the server's etag.

params.name: data.type
params.description: Required. Immutable. The type of entity.

params.name: data.asset
params.description: Required. Immutable. The ID of the asset associated with the storage location containing the entity data. The entity must be with in the same zone with the asset.

params.name: data.data_path
params.description: Required. Immutable. The storage path of the entity data. For Cloud Storage data, this is the fully-qualified path to the entity, such as gs://bucket/path/to/data. For BigQuery data, this is the name of the table resource, such as projects/project_id/datasets/dataset_id/tables/table_id.

params.name: data.data_path_pattern
params.description: Optional. The set of items within the data path constituting the data in the entity, represented as a glob path. Example: gs://bucket/path/to/data/**/*.csv.

params.name: data.catalog_entry
params.description: Output only. The name of the associated Data Catalog entry.

params.name: data.system
params.description: Required. Immutable. Identifies the storage system of the entity data.

params.name: data.format
params.description: Required. Identifies the storage format of the entity data. It does not apply to entities with data stored in BigQuery.

params.name: data.compatibility
params.description: Output only. Metadata stores that the entity is compatible with.

params.name: data.schema
params.description: Required. The description of the data structure and layout. The schema is not included in list responses. It is only included in SCHEMA and FULL entity views of a GetEntity response.
